Below is a comparison of key storage account types:

| Type                | Supported Services       | Redundancy Options    | Usage                        |
| ------------------- | ------------------------ | --------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| Standard GPv2       | Blob, File, Queue, Table | LRS, ZRS, GRS, RA-GRS | General-purpose applications |
| Premium Block Blob  | Blob only                | LRS, ZRS              | High-performance analytics   |
| Premium File Shares | File only                | LRS, ZRS              | Enterprise file workloads    |

For example, GPv2 is used for general applications, while premium options are used for performance-critical workloads.

A real-life use case is choosing premium storage for real-time applications and standard storage for backups.

Another example is enterprises mixing storage types based on workload requirements.

This comparison helps in selecting the right storage type.
